# Frontend UI (GAS HTML Service)

## Structure

- `Index.html` — static DOM skeleton, nav, page containers, element IDs referenced by `Script.html`.
- `Script.html` — all client behavior; use `runServer()` wrapper around `google.script.run`.
- `Style.html` — CSS only; keep responsive grid fixes here.

When adding UI, add the DOM node in `Index.html`, wire behavior in `Script.html`, style in `Style.html`.

## State and Writes

After any successful save/update/archive, call `syncDataAfterWrite_()` — do not only invalidate flags without reloading dashboard/database views.

```javascript
// ✅ GOOD
runServer('saveProject', [payload], function () {
  syncDataAfterWrite_();
  showToast('Saved.', 'success');
});

// ❌ BAD — stale lists after write
AppState.loaded.database = false;
```

Key client caches: `AppState.projectRows`, `AppState.supportRows`, `AppState.dashboardData`.

## Forms and Hierarchy

- Build controls from field config arrays (`HEADER_FIELDS`, `PO_FIELDS`, etc.).
- Key expanded/collapsed UI state by instance IDs, not batch/MO/PO display values.
- Guard destructive actions (`Clear`) with confirmation modals.
- Use semantic chart colors from `CHART_CONFIGS`, not enumeration index.

## Filters and Search

- Empty search must match all rows; never normalize empty input to `N/A`.
- Exports (`exportDatabaseExcel`, `exportSupportExcel`) must use the same filtered row set shown in the table.

## Responsive Layout

For grids and dashboard cards that overflow with real data:

```css
grid-template-columns: repeat(N, minmax(0, 1fr));
/* nested children */
min-width: 0;
```

Test desktop and mobile with long product names and populated charts.

## Do Not

- Expose raw audit JSON to users — render business-readable summaries.
- Add page-specific sheet-read or transport workarounds; fix shared helpers in `Code.gs` instead.
